<article id="post-296" class="post-296 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-blog post clearfix cat-10">
		
	<span class="post-icon"></span><!-- /post-icon -->

	<!-- post-title -->
								<h1 class="post-title"><a href="http://evoke.ics.uci.edu/computer-science-as-a-general-education-requirement/">Computer Science as a General Education Requirement?</a></h1>
						<!-- /post-title -->

	<!-- post-meta -->
	<p class="post-meta"> 
					<time datetime="2012-04-02" class="post-date" pubdate>Apr 2, 2012</time>
		
						<span class="post-author"><a href="http://evoke.ics.uci.edu/author/sslota/" title="Posts by Steve Slota" rel="author">Steve Slota</a></span>
				<span class="post-category"><a href="http://evoke.ics.uci.edu/category/blog/" title="View all posts in Blog" rel="category tag">Blog</a></span>
									<span class="post-comment"><a href="http://evoke.ics.uci.edu/computer-science-as-a-general-education-requirement/#respond" title="Comment on Computer Science as a General Education Requirement?">No Comments</a></span>
										    
	</p>
	<!-- /post-meta -->
	
	
<!-- post-image -->
<!-- /post-image -->

<!-- post-content -->

	<p>&#8220;Earning a <a href="http://colleges.usnews.rankingsandreviews.com/best-colleges">college degree</a> often involves completing a list of general education requirements. Aimed at turning out well-rounded graduates, the mandated curriculum can include groups of courses from a variety of disciplines—literature, philosophy, social and physical sciences, history, and foreign languages.</p>
<p>As we continue on a track where technology powers everything from our toothbrushes to our <a href="http://www.usnews.com/education/best-colleges/articles/2012/02/07/digital-print-textbooks-to-compete-for-college-audience">textbooks</a>, should computer science be added to the list?&#8221;</p>
<p><a href="http://www.usnews.com/education/best-colleges/articles/2012/04/03/computer-science-transitions-from-elective-to-requirement-computer-science-transitions-from-elective-to-requirement">http://www.usnews.com/education/best-colleges/articles/2012/04/03/computer-science-transitions-from-elective-to-requirement-computer-science-transitions-from-elective-to-requirement</a></p>
<p>Our own Geof Bowker was interviewed for this article.</p>

<!-- /post-content -->	
		
    </article>
<!-- /post -->
	
			
				
